KAIZER Chiefs went into the halftime break leading Orlando Pirates 2-1 at halftime in a pulsating Soweto derby clash in the Absa Premiership on Saturday. Ntsikelelo Nyauza who was the captain in place of suspended Happy Jele, headed the ball into his own net as goalkeeper Wayne Sandilands was not on his line in the first minute giving the Amakhosi a perfect start in under 50 seconds. Leonardo Castro, who put Nyauza under pressure to make the mistake that lead to a goal scored on the 28 minute to make it 2-0. The Buccaneers hit back seven minutes before the break when a free-kick on the near side from Vincent Pule went in to the far corner after sneaking in from the near post.